(24086, 292244, 'rssmi_item_description', 'a:1:{i:0;a:11:{s:9:"mystrdate";i:1434510020;s:7:"mytitle";s:27:"‘Press pause’ on border";s:6:"mylink";s:66:"http://www.opendevelopmentcambodia.net/news/press-pause-on-border/";s:6:"mydesc";s:697:"<p>Opposition lawmakers said they will demand that Prime Minister Hun Sen halt ongoing efforts to demarcate Cambodia&rsquo;s border with Vietnam until after the 2018 election to guarantee a consensus on the controversial boundary. This came as the Ministry of Foreign Affairs yesterday again moved to reinforce its stance against Vietnamese encroachment.</p>\n<p>News of the request also came as authorities confirmed a local border police chief in Ratanakkiri province&rsquo;s O&rsquo;Yadav district had been removed for allowing the Vietnamese to build at least nine irrigation ponds inside the yet-to-be delineated &ldquo;white&rdquo; zone near Pak Nhai commune&rsquo;s Lom village. &hellip;</p>";s:7:"myimage";N;s:8:"myAuthor";s:11:"Ratana Pich";s:12:"itemcategory";s:92:"Cambodia National Rescue Party, Hor Namhong, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Um Sam An, Vietnam";s:7:"mycatid";N;s:7:"myGroup";N;s:6:"feedID";i:53127;s:13:"useMediaImage";i:0;}}'),
