(27381, 293072, 'rssmi_item_description', 'a:1:{i:0;a:11:{s:9:"mystrdate";i:1434619469;s:7:"mytitle";s:58:"Military Court Sentences Soldier to 7 Years for Misconduct";s:6:"mylink";s:94:"http://www.irrawaddy.org/burma/military-court-sentences-soldier-to-7-years-for-misconduct.html";s:6:"mydesc";s:2439:"<div><a href="http://www.irrawaddy.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Women.jpg"><img src="http://www.irrawaddy.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Women.jpg" alt="Women march for peace and gender justice in Rangoon in 2012. (Photo: JPaing / The Irrawaddy)" width="610" height="407"></a><p>Women march for peace and gender justice in Rangoon in 2012. (Photo: JPaing / The Irrawaddy)</p></div>\n<p>RANGOON &mdash; A military court in northern Burma this week sentenced a Burmese soldier to seven years in prison on three charges of misconduct, but dismissed allegations that he attempted to rape a 73-year-old ethnic Kachin woman.</p>\n<p>The 24-year-old soldier was a member of the Burma Army&rsquo;s Light Infantry Battalion No. 438, stationed Winemaw Township in conflict-torn Kachin State. Following accusations of the attempted rape and demands for a civilian trial, he was removed from service and brought before a military court.</p>\n<p>Police informed the Kachin Baptist Convention (KBC), a local religious humanitarian aid group, that the soldier was sentenced on Monday after being found guilty of trespassing, use of illegal drugs and violation of the military code of conduct.</p>\n<p>Htoi San Raw, a Kachin women&rsquo;s rights activist who is affiliated with KBC, told The Irrawaddy on Thursday that the community is dissatisfied with the outcome, renewing calls for a civilian trial and sexual assault charges.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;We asked [the Burma Army] to hand him over to the public courts, but they didn&rsquo;t do it,&rdquo; Htoi San Raw said. &ldquo;If we can bring him to a public court we can charge him for trying to rape someone.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>Last month, hundreds gathered in protest in the remote township to demand justice for the alleged assault on an elderly Kachin woman on April 13 of this year.</p>\n<p>Further south, in the northern reaches of Shan State, Kachin villagers still await justice for the alleged rape and murder of two young Kachin volunteer teachers in late January. A government-led investigation is still ongoing amid accusations by local villagers that the gruesome act may have been committed by Burma Army troops.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.irrawaddy.org/burma/military-court-sentences-soldier-to-7-years-for-misconduct.html">Military Court Sentences Soldier to 7 Years for Misconduct</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.irrawaddy.org/">The Irrawaddy</a>.</p>";s:7:"myimage";N;s:8:"myAuthor";s:3:"T G";s:12:"itemcategory";s:70:"A_Factiva, Burma, Women, NANG SENG NOM &amp; LAWI WENG / THE IRRAWADDY";s:7:"mycatid";N;s:7:"myGroup";N;s:6:"feedID";i:53149;s:13:"useMediaImage";i:0;}}'),
