(31562, 294113, 'rssmi_item_description', 'a:1:{i:0;a:11:{s:9:"mystrdate";i:1434695839;s:7:"mytitle";s:63:"Suu Kyi Calls for ‘Clean Politics’ in 70th Birthday Message";s:6:"mylink";s:93:"http://www.irrawaddy.org/burma/suu-kyi-calls-for-clean-politics-in-70th-birthday-message.html";s:6:"mydesc";s:2763:"<div><a href="http://www.irrawaddy.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Suu-Kyi.jpg"><img src="http://www.irrawaddy.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Suu-Kyi.jpg" alt="Burmese democracy leader Aung San Suu Kyi, who turns 70 today, at a Rangoon press conference in 1997. (Photo: Patrick De Noirmont / Reuters)" width="610" height="445"></a><p>Burmese democracy leader Aung San Suu Kyi, who turns 70 today, at a Rangoon press conference in 1997. (Photo: Patrick De Noirmont / Reuters)</p></div>\n<p>RANGOON&mdash;Burma&rsquo;s opposition leader Aung San Suu Kyi has used a video message recorded for her 70th birthday on Friday to call for &lsquo;clean politics&rsquo; ahead of the general election this year.</p>\n<p>In the 10-minute, Burmese language message posted on the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/NLDParty?fref=ts">National League for Democracy Facebook </a>page, Suu Kyi thanked the public for their support and urged them to act lawfully and in unity to ensure Burma&rsquo;s stability and development.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Please don&rsquo;t cheat people. Please avoid dishonest means for your party&rsquo;s success. This year is very important,&rdquo; she said.</p>\n<p>The Nobel laureate said that the poll would determine the future of the country for the years to come and the country was at a crossroads on par with that of 1947&rsquo;s independence declaration.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;How the election will be held, what the results will be and what Burma will look like after the elections will decide Burma&rsquo;s future for years to come, not only for this year,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;People will have to decide which road they want Burma to take. Please take a long view, whatever you do.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>She added that she has learned after near 30 years on the political stage that every person had an ability to make a contribution to their country and the world.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Whether you are in a humble or high position, please think seriously about what you could do for the country. Don&rsquo;t think about what you need. Think about the people around you, the world and mankind. We can&rsquo;t be isolated from the outside world,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;If I get the chance to live for another 20 years, I want to see Burma developed and I want the Burmese people to be respected by the world.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>Suu Kyi will celebrate her birthday in Naypyidaw today before traveling to Rangoon for a meeting of the NLD central executive committee on Saturday.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.irrawaddy.org/burma/suu-kyi-calls-for-clean-politics-in-70th-birthday-message.html">Suu Kyi Calls for &lsquo;Clean Politics&rsquo; in 70th Birthday Message</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.irrawaddy.org/">The Irrawaddy</a>.</p>";s:7:"myimage";N;s:8:"myAuthor";s:3:"T G";s:12:"itemcategory";s:31:"A_Factiva, Burma, THE IRRAWADDY";s:7:"mycatid";N;s:7:"myGroup";N;s:6:"feedID";i:53149;s:13:"useMediaImage";i:0;}}'),
