(31642, 294133, 'rssmi_item_description', 'a:1:{i:0;a:11:{s:9:"mystrdate";i:1434942050;s:7:"mytitle";s:49:"Cambodia priced out of Filipino rice tender again";s:6:"mylink";s:94:"http://www.opendevelopmentcambodia.net/news/cambodia-priced-out-of-filipino-rice-tender-again/";s:6:"mydesc";s:506:"<p>Cambodia has lost a 100,000-tonne Filipino rice bid to Vietnam, on account of a higher costs as compared to regional competitors, marking the fourth time the Kingdom has failed to win a rice tender issued by the Philippines.</p>\n<p>The Philippines National Food Authority last week awarded the tender to Vietnam Southern Food Corp based on its offer of $416.85 per tonne, a little higher than the reference price of $408.15 per tonne set during the tender, according to the Philippine Star. &hellip;</p>";s:7:"myimage";N;s:8:"myAuthor";s:11:"Ratana Pich";s:12:"itemcategory";s:99:"Cambodia Rice Federation (CRF), Philippines National Food Authority, Sok Puthyvuth, The Philippines";s:7:"mycatid";N;s:7:"myGroup";N;s:6:"feedID";i:53127;s:13:"useMediaImage";i:0;}}'),
