(33154, 294508, 'rssmi_item_description', 'a:1:{i:0;a:11:{s:9:"mystrdate";i:1434195072;s:7:"mytitle";s:50:"Want to Unpack ASEAN? Send Us Your Story Proposal!";s:6:"mylink";s:74:"http://www.aseannews.net/want-to-unpack-asean-send-us-your-story-proposal/";s:6:"mydesc";s:2588:"<p>BANGKOK/MANILA &ndash; 2015 is the year the &lsquo;ASEAN Community&rsquo; is to be formed, but do we really have enough in common to be a community? Think of a good story idea that investigates and unpacks an ASEAN-related news issue, and send it to us at the &lsquo;<a href="http://www.aseannews.net/" target="_blank">Reporting ASEAN: 2015 and Beyond</a>&rsquo; fellowship program!</p>\n<p>The calls for applications can be downloaded <a title="Calls Reporting ASEAN June 2015" href="http://www.aseannews.net/wp-content/uploads/Calls-for-Stories-Reporting-ASEAN-Jun-2015.pdf" target="_blank">here.<br></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.aseannews.net/following-the-asean-beat/01-3/" rel="attachment wp-att-1672"><span></span></a> &nbsp;<a href="http://www.aseannews.net/following-the-asean-beat/01-4/" rel="attachment wp-att-1673"><img title="01" src="http://www.aseannews.net/wp-content/uploads/013-201x300.png" alt="" width="201" height="300"></a>&nbsp; Applications are to be received by 15 July 2015 for this round of calls. Journalists eligible to apply are those from the 10 member countries of ASEAN, from print, photojournalism or television backgrounds.</p>\n<p>Accepted fellows in the reporting series will get support to report on the approved stories that focus on ASEAN integration and regionalism as well as the challenges these bring.</p>\n<p>Application and story proposal forms may be filled up at <a title="Online form Reporting ASEAN" href="http://bit.ly/reportingasean" target="_blank">http://bit.ly/reportingasean</a> or downloaded in Word format <a title="Application and Story Forms Reporting ASEAN" href="http://www.aseannews.net/wp-content/uploads/Application-and-Story-Proposal-Forms-Final-No-Date.doc" target="_blank">here</a>. Inquiries may be sent to <a href="mailto:reportingasean@gmail.com">reportingasean@gmail.com</a>, <a href="mailto:ipsasiapacificdesk@me.com">ipsasiapacificdesk@me.com</a> and @reportingasean.</p>\n<p>The &lsquo;Reporting ASEAN: 2015 and Beyond&rsquo; program is implemented by <a title="IPS Asia-Pacific" href="http://www.ipsnewsasia.net/" target="_blank">IPS Asia-Pacific </a>news organization and <a href="http://www.probefound.com/" target="_blank">Probe Media Foundation Inc</a>, two Asia-based organizations that work on media development and capacity-building in the region.</p>\n<p>The program is supported by the<a href="http://www.aseanfoundation.org/" target="_blank"> ASEAN Foundation</a> and the ASEAN-Japan Solidarity Fund and the <a href="http://www.rockefellerfoundation.org/" target="_blank">Rockefeller Foundation</a>.</p>";s:7:"myimage";N;s:8:"myAuthor";s:9:"Admin IPS";s:12:"itemcategory";s:74:"Features, Fellowship applications, Reporting ASEAN: 2015 and Beyond Series";s:7:"mycatid";s:1:"5";s:7:"myGroup";s:10:"ASEAN News";s:6:"feedID";i:53203;s:13:"useMediaImage";i:0;}}'),
